<p>Inland neighborhoods such as Scripps Ranch, Rancho Penasquitos, and Carmel Mountain Ranch experience higher temperatures and greater cooling demands, making larger solar systems and higher-capacity HVAC equipment more beneficial. These areas typically have newer homes with better insulation and more suitable roof orientations for solar installations.</p>

